03-jun-2026:  Claude Code
	* v2.3.2 (unreleased) - Code quality improvements and expanded test coverage.
	  Refactored bam_file_to_idx with robust exception handling (nested try/finally
	  for guaranteed FIFO cleanup). Converted string concatenation to f-strings in
	  export functions. Extracted magic number 1024*256 to READ_BUFFER_SIZE constant.
	  Renamed class from bamlorenzcoverage to BamLorenzCoverage (PEP 8 compliance).
	  Fixed CLI option parsing (removed nargs=1). Fixed undefined variable in stats
	  output by restructuring code flow. Added 10 new comprehensive tests covering
	  export functions (TSV format, file I/O), error handling (empty dict, extreme
	  coverage, boundary values), and SVG rendering (file creation, XML validity,
	  precision handling). Fixed flake8 E402 by combining duplicate docstrings.
	  Added global permission rules denying automatic test execution.

02-jun-2026:  Youri Hoogstrate
	* v2.3.1 - Modernised packaging (setup.py -> pyproject.toml), replaced
	  Travis CI with GitHub Actions, CLI entry point moved to blc/cli.py.
	  Fixed bug where Ctrl+C did not terminate child process before cleanup.
	  Fixed docstring inaccuracy in estimate_lorenz_curves (1/16 -> 1/7).
	  Performance improvements in bam_file_to_idx: larger read buffer
	  (4KB -> 256KB), defaultdict, int parsing per line, rpartition.
	  Legacy methods (bam_file_to_idx_old, bam_file_to_idx_slow_and_mem_unsafe,
	  bam_file_to_idx_mem_unsafe, coverage_file_to_idx) marked deprecated.
	  Removed unused dependencies numpy and tqdm from pyproject.toml.

13-sept-2018:  Youri Hoogstrate
	* v2.3.0 - Adds arguments -r/--region and -b/--bed-regions to target
	  specific genomic regions. This way alternative loci can be
	  excluded for instance.

13-sept-2018:  Youri Hoogstrate
	* v2.2.0 - Removes --roc argument and adds multiple statistics
	   including ROC to the -s/--stats argument.

11-sept-2018:  Youri Hoogstrate
	* v2.1.0 - Adds unit tests and can calculate ROC for Lorenz curves

05-sept-2018:  Youri Hoogstrate
	* v2.0.0 - does not require to use samtools, does not take all
	  pysam.samtools.depth output into memory, does not export
	  pysam.samtools.depth to a file but uses parallelized thread
	  that writes to a FIFO.
